SIMPLE: miraculous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Miraculous
<hw>Mi*rac"u*lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>miraculeux</ets>. See <er>Miracle</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of the nature of a miracle; performed by
supernatural power; effected by the direct agency of almighty power, and
not by natural causes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Supernatural; wonderful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Wonder-working.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>miraculous</xex> harp.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Mi*rac"u*lous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Mi*rac"u*lous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mirador</ent>⟦br⟧
